@startuml

title Inventory Admin Sequence Diagram

actor "Inventory Admin" as Admin
participant "Frontend Website" as Frontend
participant "Apache\n(HTTP Server)" as Apache

box "Laravel Application" #LightGreen
  participant "Middleware" as MW
  participant "Controller" as C
  participant "Inventory Service" as Service
  participant "Eloquent ORM" as ORM
end box

database "MariaDB Database" as DB

note right of Admin
Inventory Admin can perform
regular inventory user viewing actions,
such as browsing and checking inventory.

It is assumed the Inventory
Admin is authenticated/authorized

This diagram only shows
additional administrative actions.
end note


== Update Inventory (Add / Delete Item) ==
Admin -> Frontend: Add or delete inventory item
activate Admin
activate Frontend

Frontend -> Apache: POST /admin/items/update
activate Apache
Apache -> MW: Forward request
deactivate Apache
note left of DB
IMPORTANT: This sequence assumes normal system operation. If a failure
occurs at any layer, the system returns an error message
and prompts the user to retry.
end note
activate MW
MW -> C: Pass validated request
deactivate MW

activate C
C -> Service: updateInventory()
activate Service

Service -> ORM: Insert or delete item
activate ORM
ORM -> DB: Insert or delete inventory record
activate DB
DB --> ORM: Update success
deactivate DB
ORM --> Service: Update persisted
deactivate ORM

Service --> C: Update confirmation
deactivate Service
C --> Frontend: Response
deactivate C

Frontend --> Admin: Display update result
deactivate Frontend
deactivate Admin

== Cancel Borrow or Special Request ==
Admin -> Frontend: Cancel request
activate Admin
activate Frontend

Frontend -> Apache: POST /admin/cancelRequest
activate Apache
Apache -> MW: Forward request
deactivate Apache

activate MW
MW -> C: Pass validated request
deactivate MW

activate C
C -> Service: cancelRequest()
activate Service

Service -> ORM: Update request status [Cancelled]
activate ORM
ORM -> DB: Update request record
activate DB
DB --> ORM: Update success
deactivate DB
ORM --> Service: Status updated
deactivate ORM

Service --> C: Cancellation confirmation
deactivate Service
C --> Frontend: Response
deactivate C

Frontend --> Admin: Display confirmation
deactivate Frontend
deactivate Admin

== View and Download Inventory Statistics ==
Admin -> Frontend: Request statistics
activate Admin
activate Frontend

Frontend -> Apache: GET /admin/statistics
activate Apache
Apache -> MW: Forward request
deactivate Apache

activate MW
MW -> C: Pass validated request
deactivate MW

activate C
C -> Service: generateStatistics()
activate Service

Service -> ORM: Query usage data
activate ORM
ORM -> DB: Select inventory usage data
activate DB
DB --> ORM: Inventory statistics
deactivate DB
ORM --> Service: Statistics dataset
deactivate ORM

Service --> C: Statistics report
deactivate Service
C --> Frontend: Report data
deactivate C

Frontend --> Admin: Display / Download report
deactivate Frontend
deactivate Admin

== Search and Ban User ==
Admin -> Frontend: Search for user
activate Admin
activate Frontend

Frontend -> Apache: GET /admin/users?search
activate Apache
Apache -> MW: Forward request
deactivate Apache

activate MW
MW -> C: Pass validated request
deactivate MW

activate C
C -> Service: searchUsers()
activate Service

Service -> ORM: Query users
activate ORM
ORM -> DB: Select matching users
activate DB
DB --> ORM: User list
deactivate DB
ORM --> Service: User collection
deactivate ORM

Service --> C: User list
deactivate Service
C --> Frontend: User results
deactivate C

Frontend --> Admin: Display users
deactivate Frontend
deactivate Admin

Admin -> Frontend: Select user and ban
activate Admin
activate Frontend

Frontend -> Apache: POST /admin/banUser
activate Apache
Apache -> MW: Forward request
deactivate Apache

activate MW
MW -> C: Pass validated request
deactivate MW

activate C
C -> Service: banUser(userID)
activate Service

Service -> ORM: Update user status [Banned]
activate ORM
ORM -> DB: Update user record
activate DB
DB --> ORM: Update success
deactivate DB
ORM --> Service: Ban persisted
deactivate ORM

Service --> C: Ban confirmation
deactivate Service
C --> Frontend: Response
deactivate C

Frontend --> Admin: Display confirmation
deactivate Frontend
deactivate Admin

@enduml